SIMPLE: thump
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thump
<hw>Thump</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably of imitative
origin; perhaps influenced by <ets>dump</ets>, v. t.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The sound made by the sudden fall or blow of a heavy body, as of a
hammer, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The distant forge's swinging <qex>thump</qex> profound.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With heavy <qex>thump</qex>, a lifeless lump,⟦br⟧
They dropped down, one by one.</q> <rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A blow or knock, as with something blunt or heavy; a
heavy fall.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The watchman gave so great a <qex>thump</qex> at my door, that I
awaked at the knock.</q> <rj><qau>Tatler.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thump</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Thump
<hw>Thump</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Thumped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Thumping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To strike or beat with something
thick or heavy, or so as to cause a dull sound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These bastard Bretons; whom our hathers⟦br⟧
Have in their own land beaten, bobbed, and <qex>thumped</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thump</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Thump
<hw>Thump</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To give a thump or thumps; to
strike or fall with a heavy blow; to pound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A watchman at midnight <qex>thumps</qex> with his pole.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thumper</ent>⟦br⟧
